The Japanese Wife|Aparna Sen Bengali Film|E-Subs|DDR|Phantom

The Japanese Wife is a 2010 Indian film directed by Bengali filmmaker Aparna Sen. It stars Rahul Bose, Raima Sen and Moushumi Chatterjee, and Japanese actress Chigusa Takaku in the title role. It is in English, Bengali and Japanese.

The story revolves around a young Bengali village school teacher (Rahul Bose) marrying his Japanese pen friend (Chigusa Takaku) over letters and remaining true and loyal to her throughout his life, while actually never meeting her.

Thanks to DDR-Kamal for the excellent rip.

Sample file included.

Awards:
1.Star Entertainment Award for Best Film
2.Star Entertainment Award for Best Director, Aparna Sen
3.Star Entertainment Award for Best Cinematography, Anay Goswamy
4.Best Film Award at the 2010 Hidden Gems Film Festival
5.Silver Crow Pheasant Award (Audience Choice) at 2010 International Film Festival of Kerala

Cast:
Rahul Bose as Snehamoy Chatterjee
Raima Sen as Sandhya
